{
  "text": " I'm an eight generation direct descendant to the very first free black African-American to purchase property on Staten Island. They came and traveled here in 1799 and purchased their piece of land in Sandy Ground in the Rossville area in 1828. I opened this restaurant with $22,000, no resources. The world was pretty much down. There was nobody out here really to help us. And I called every agency in the world to seek some support, resources, capital and direction. And that did not exist. And so I did everything ground up grassroots on my own with my husband and my children, just trying to figure things out. And that's how this kitchen came about. Thank you so much. Thank you. I appreciate you.",
